HEADWORD: Lacteous
<hw>Lac"te*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[See
<er>Lacteal</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Milky; resembling milk.</def>
⟦ldquo⟧The <xex>lacteous</xex> circle.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Lacteal; conveying chyle; <as>as, <ex>lacteous</ex>
vessels</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lacteously</ent>⟦br⟧
